  "texts": [
    "Similar to Sect. 2.4, multiplying by N i=1 (z i -z) 2 yields a polynomial of degree 2N.",
    "All critical curves can be found by solving for all the roots ϕ = 0 and then tracing all critical curves for 0 <= ϕ <= 2π.",
    "This can be easily achieved using a simple root-finder like the Newton-Raphson method.",
    "In the left panel of Fig. 4 the critical lines for the N = 50 stars were calculated in this way by starting at the 2 N = 100 complex roots and following the critical curves for ϕ between 0 and 2π.",
    "The corresponding caustic lines in the source plane can be found by mapping the critical lines using the microlensing equation Eq."
